text: The implicit European extinctionism among the superficially non-hostile liberal intellectual elite is quite mind-melting. "They just stopped breeding, so I guess they have to disappear. Oh well." ...
... WTF is this? Conformism mostly, but to something so radically genocidal by essence it's simply stunning.
If you think survival of European people is okay, you're far right now. You know this, of course, but it's worth noting how far into the European Extinction Project we've gone.
If you think the extinction of European peoples is not a great thing to be publicly celebrated the EU wants, at least, to silence you, and probably jail you. Quite wild this seems at all normal.

"The New Europeans"
If you're the Old Europeans, i.e. actual Europeans, it sounds very clearly as if they're dedicated to your eradication.
Do the counter-revolution with maximum urgency and intensity. We can apologize later if necessary. (It won't be.)
Given our eschatological situation, we run out of time before over-reaction becomes a serious problem. (So reaction without serious inhibition is theologically vindicated.)
